days.dailyDigest: Today saw major announcements around GPT-5's multimodal capabilities and a new open-source robotics foundation model. The AI community is buzzing about benchmark results and real-world applications.

videos.title: GPT-5 Is Here - Everything You Need To Know
videos.summary:
• GPT-5 features native multimodal understanding across text, images, audio, and video
• Reasoning benchmarks show 40% improvement over GPT-4o on complex math and coding tasks
• Pricing is 2x cheaper per token than GPT-4o, making it more accessible
• New "deep thinking" mode enables multi-step problem solving with transparent chain-of-thought

videos.title: The Real Impact of AI Agents in 2026
videos.summary:
• AI agents are now handling 30% of customer service interactions at Fortune 500 companies
• Code generation agents have reduced development time by 50% in controlled studies
• Key limitation remains: agents still struggle with ambiguous real-world tasks requiring judgment

videos.title: This AI Robot Learns To Walk in Minutes!
videos.summary:
• New sim-to-real transfer technique enables robots to learn locomotion in under 10 minutes
• The approach uses a diffusion-based policy that generalizes across different terrain types
• Open-source foundation model released, enabling researchers worldwide to build on this work
